T1  - A Practical Alternative to Comparison Group Designs in od Evaluations: the Abbreviated Time Series Design
AU  - Armenakis, Achilles
AU  - Smith, Leigh
Y1  - 1978/09/01
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255731
DO  - 10.5465/255731
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 499
EP  - 507
VL  - 21
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article examines the use of abbreviated time series design (ATSD) as an alternative to comparison group designs in the evaluation of organization development (OD). It was found, in a study which dealt with problems in evaluating OD efforts, that some of the most significant administrative problems in evaluating change center around the difficulties of employing comparison groups. These difficulties have prompted change agents to utilize more convenient one-group designs. With the ATSD, one may be able to discount expectation effects by asking a sample of organizational members to depict situations in which change has been detected.
AB  - The article examines the use of abbreviated time series design (ATSD) as an alternative to comparison group designs in the evaluation of organization development (OD). It was found, in a study which dealt with problems in evaluating OD efforts, that some of the most significant administrative problems in evaluating change center around the difficulties of employing comparison groups. These difficulties have prompted change agents to utilize more convenient one-group designs. With the ATSD, one may be able to discount expectation effects by asking a sample of organizational members to depict situations in which change has been detected.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/255731
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/255731
