T1  - Corporate Social Responsibility and Stock Market Performance
AU  - Alexander, Gordon J.
AU  - Buchholz, Rogene A.
Y1  - 1978/09/01
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255728
DO  - 10.5465/255728
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 479
EP  - 486
VL  - 21
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article examines the relationship between social responsibility and stock market performance of corporations in the U.S. for the period 1970-1974. Risk measures and differential returns of the securities in the social responsibility surveys were calculated for the five-year sample period 1970-1974 and a three-year subperiod 1971-1973. The measures of differential return were ranked in descending order over the five and three-year periods. Rank order correlations were calculated between survey rank and differential return rank. These correlations indicate a low insignificant relationship between risk-adjusted performance and degree of social responsibility.
AB  - The article examines the relationship between social responsibility and stock market performance of corporations in the U.S. for the period 1970-1974. Risk measures and differential returns of the securities in the social responsibility surveys were calculated for the five-year sample period 1970-1974 and a three-year subperiod 1971-1973. The measures of differential return were ranked in descending order over the five and three-year periods. Rank order correlations were calculated between survey rank and differential return rank. These correlations indicate a low insignificant relationship between risk-adjusted performance and degree of social responsibility.
